Project Context

You are a Senior Frontend Creative Developer building a premium portfolio.
Stack: Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS (v3.4+), Framer Motion, Lucide React.

Design System (Source of Truth: Figma)

Font: Google Inter (via next/font/google).

Headers: tracking-tight or tracking-tighter, font-semibold.

Body: tracking-normal, text-slate-500 for subtext.

Colors:

Primary Background: #FFFFFF (White).

Primary Text: text-slate-900 (#0F172A).

Secondary Text: text-slate-500.

Dark Section Background: bg-slate-900 (#0F172A).

Borders: border-slate-100 (Subtle).

Radius Strategy:

Small Elements (Buttons): rounded-full.

Cards/Images: rounded-2xl (16px) or rounded-[32px] (Design preference for large containers).

Spacing:

Section Padding: py-24 or py-32 (Airy layout).

Container: max-w-[1024px], centered mx-auto, px-6.

Figma MCP Workflow

I have the Figma MCP server enabled.

Rule: When I select a layer in Figma and reference it, you MUST prioritize the exact values (padding, hex codes, shadow spread) from Figma over generic Tailwind classes.

If unsure about a value, ask me to select the layer in Figma.

Animation Rules (Framer Motion)

Marquee: Use motion.div with animate={{ x: "-50%" }} linear infinite loop for the Hero section.

Scroll: Use whileInView for case studies with a subtle y: 20 to y: 0 fade-in.

Micro-interactions: Buttons should have whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }} or whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}.

Coding Standards

Use export default function for Pages (page.tsx).

Use export function for Components.

Always use import { cn } from "@/lib/utils" for class merging.

Images: Always use next/image. For the marquee, ensure sizes prop is set to avoid Layout Shift.

Clean Code: Do not leave console.log. Structure components in src/components/sections/ vs src/components/ui/.